            <entry xml:id="entry_kʼūsk" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼūsk</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼoskæ</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>kʼosgæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>ниша</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>niche</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>бойница</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>loophole</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>mydy kʼūsk</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>mudi kʼoskæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ячейка в сотах</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>honeycomb</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>sisy kʼusḱy kʼūs læwwy bægænyjæ jeʒag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в стенной нише стоит чаша, полная пива</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>in a wall niche there is a bowl full of beer</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            155</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kælmiti kʼosgiti banixasuncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гусениц (пчелиных) залепляют в сотовые ячейки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(bee) caterpillars are being stuck in honeycombs</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III
                            66</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>köšk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kūšk</w>
                        <gloss><q>павильон</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>киоск</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>вышка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>башня</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kōšk</w></mentioned> id. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр.
                            292</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                            292</biblScope></bibl>). Отсюда и слово %iкиоск%i в европейских языках,
                    а также <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>k’osk’i</w>
                        <gloss><q>башня</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"><lang/>
                        <w>k’wašk</w>
                        <gloss><q>господский дом</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Mészaros"/><biblScope>356</biblScope></bibl>).
                    Первоисточником следует считать <mentioned xml:lang="ira-x-mid"><lang/>
                        <w>*gōšak</w></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>gōša</w>
                        <gloss><q>угол</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>уголок</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>уединенное место</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>211</biblScope></bibl>). Любопытно,
                    что значение ‘ниша’ в осетинском стоит ближе к исходному персидскому ‘уголок’ и
                    пр., чем к позднейшим ‘павильон’, ‘дворец’, ‘башня’ и пр. Не говорит ли это о
                    давности усвоения этого слова в осетинском?</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>köšk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kūšk</w>
                        <gloss><q>pavilion</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>kiosk</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>tower</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kōšk</w></mentioned> id. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KPF"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр.
                            292</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                            292</biblScope></bibl>). The word %ikiosk%i in European languages is
                    also from it, as well as <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>k’osk’i</w>
                        <gloss><q>tower</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"><lang/>
                        <w>k’wašk</w>
                        <gloss><q>manor house</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Mészaros"/><biblScope>356</biblScope></bibl>). The primary
                    origin should be considered <mentioned xml:lang="ira-x-mid"><lang/>
                        <w>*gōšak</w></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>gōša</w>
                        <gloss><q>corner</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>nook</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>secluded place</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>211</biblScope></bibl>). It is
                    interesting that the meaning ‘niche’ in Ossetic is closer to the original
                    Persian meaning ‘corner’ etc., than to the later meanings ‘pavilion’, ‘palace’,
                    ‘tower’ etc. Does this mean that the word was acquired long ago in
                    Ossetic?</etym>
            </entry>
